# Python Async Patterns (aiogram 3.x)

## Never block the event loop

```python
# ❌ BAD — blocks event loop
import time
time.sleep(2)
result = requests.get(url)

# ✅ GOOD — async I/O
import asyncio
import aiohttp
await asyncio.sleep(2)
async with aiohttp.ClientSession() as s:
    result = await s.get(url)
```

## Heavy CPU work (STT model inference) — use executor

```python
# ❌ BAD — freezes bot during transcription
text = whisper_model.transcribe(audio_path)

# ✅ GOOD — offload to thread pool
loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()
text = await loop.run_in_executor(None, whisper_model.transcribe, audio_path)
```

## Handler signature

```python
# Always async, always typed
@dp.message(F.voice)
async def handle_voice(message: types.Message, bot: Bot) -> None:
    ...
```

## Database — always await aiosqlite

```python
async with aiosqlite.connect(DB_PATH) as db:
    await db.execute("INSERT ...", (val,))
    await db.commit()
```

## APScheduler with asyncio

Use `AsyncIOScheduler`, not `BackgroundScheduler`.
